  <front>
   <head>SONNET XI.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">YOung, fair, and good! ah why should young and fair</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And good be huddled in untimely grave?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Must so sweet flow'r so brief a period have,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Just bloom and charm, then fade and disappear?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Yet our's the loss, who ill alas can spare</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The bright example, which thy virtues gave;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The guerdon thine, whom gracious heav'n did save</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From longer trial in this vale of care.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rest then, sweet saint, in peace and honour rest,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While our true tears bedew thy maiden hearse,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Light lie the earth upon thy lovely breast;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And let a grateful heart with grief oppress'd</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To thy dear mem'ry consecrate this verse,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Though all too mean for who deserves the best.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
